02. Print the Characters (For Loop)

Write a program that reads a string and prints each character of the given string on a new line.

Note
Use the For loop to iterate over the string.

Input
The input will be a single line containing a string.

Output
The output should contain all the characters of the given string with each characte on a new line.

Explanation
For example, if the given string is python,
• The characters in the string python are p, y, t, h, o, and n.
The output should be,
p
y
t
h
o
n

Sample Input 1:

python

Sample Output 1:

p
y
t
h
o
n

Sample Input 2:

Variable

Sample Output 2:

V
a
r
i
a
b
l
e

Solution

string = input()

for each_char in string:
    print(each_char)
